title: For Sale:  South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit Class
location: Horry, Georgetown and surrounding counties, Myrtle Beach, South Carolina
postcontent:
Concealed Weapons Permit - 8 Hour Course

The South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit Course qualifies you to obtain your SC CWP and meet the minimum training requirements of the South Carolina law pertaining to carrying a Concealed Weapon.  The difference between our basic course and some of the others you will find is that we ensure that you are comfortable with your abilities before sending you on your way 
We cover the content required by the State of South Carolina to obtain your Concealed Weapons Permit.  The SC CWP course is 8 hours long and includes classroom instruction and a portion on the range.
You will participate in a live fire range exercise in which you will become more confident in your abilities to hit a target at ranges from 3 yards to 15 yards. The live fire exercise is a standard course of fire outlined by SLED and is 50 rounds.  Upon successful completion of the range firing, you will have met all the requirements for the training required to obtain your South Carolina Concealed Weapons permit. 
You are encouraged to bring the firearm you wish to carry to the class, but if you have not yet obtained one, you may use our firearms to become familiar with the makes and models often used. This will allow you to make better decisions on what handgun will best fit your physical size and method of carry for your CWP.  You will need to bring 50 rounds of ammunition for your weapon if are going to shoot it for the course of fire, and if you desire to use one of our guns we will have the appropriate ammunition for the gun.
We will perform the administrative tasks of completing your fingerprint card and assist you in filling out the application forms to be submitted to SLED to obtain your SC CWP.  Additionally we will take care of printing the required picture you will need to submit with your application to SLED along with notarizing the copy of your drivers license.a

You will be required to submit all the documents required to SLED after the completion of this class with the $50 fee to obtain your South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit. 
Please call REDACTED or visit our website at www.shooting-solutions.com to register online for any of our classes, including the Utah non-resident class.

title: For Sale:  South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit classes and more
location: Horry and surrounding counties, Florence, South Carolina
postcontent:
Concealed Weapons Permit - 8 Hour Course

The South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit Course qualifies you to obtain your SC CWP and meet the minimum training requirements of the South Carolina law pertaining to carrying a Concealed Weapon. The difference between our basic course and some of the others you will find is that we ensure that you are comfortable with your abilities before sending you on your way 
We cover the content required by the State of South Carolina to obtain your Concealed Weapons Permit. The SC CWP course is 8 hours long and includes classroom instruction and a portion on the range.
You will participate in a live fire range exercise in which you will become more confident in your abilities to hit a target at ranges from 3 yards to 15 yards. The live fire exercise is a standard course of fire outlined by SLED and is 50 rounds. Upon successful completion of the range firing, you will have met all the requirements for the training required to obtain your South Carolina Concealed Weapons permit. 
You are encouraged to bring the firearm you wish to carry to the class, but if you have not yet obtained one, you may use our firearms to become familiar with the makes and models often used. This will allow you to make better decisions on what handgun will best fit your physical size and method of carry for your CWP. You will need to bring 50 rounds of ammunition for your weapon if are going to shoot it for the course of fire, and if you desire to use one of our guns we will have the appropriate ammunition for the gun.
We will perform the administrative tasks of completing your fingerprint card and assist you in filling out the application forms to be submitted to SLED to obtain your SC CWP. Additionally we will take care of printing the required picture you will need to submit with your application to SLED along with notarizing the copy of your drivers license.a

You will be required to submit all the documents required to SLED after the completion of this class with the $50 fee to obtain your South Carolina Concealed Weapons Permit. 
Please call REDACTED or visit our website at www.shooting-solutions.com to register online for any of our classes, including the Utah non-resident class.

The Hellfire trigger system is a small metal piece that attaches behind the trigger of your semi auto pistol or rifle

It has a finger that presses against the back of your trigger and is adjustable.

The effect is to increase the force of the return to the forward position.

This allows the Hellfire system to shoot your gun at faster rates will even thou you are still pulling the trigger each time.

New never used. By both for 80.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Help with the John Morse Recall! Take back our state!
postcontent:
https://www.basicfreedomdefensefund.org/

https://www.facebook.com/ColoradoAccountability

On Tuesday, June 18th, our Secretary of State certified the sufficiency of our recall signatures. Of the 16,000 that were submitted, 10,000 were approved - about a 35% rejection rate, higher than average but slightly below our worst-case expectation. If we had not had the funds from you guys allowing us to hire more signature gatherers, we would NOT have made the cut. So before anything else, thank you.

Unfortunately, though, it's not over. In fact, it's looking like we're just getting started. Within minutes of the SecState's announcement, Morse's people declared that they were filing a legal challenge to the petition. Their argument is about as lame as you can get while remaining legal - literally, that we failed to "expressly include a demand for the election of a successor" in our verbiage, even though the successor election is part and parcel of a recall. But it doesn't have to have much merit. It’s a disposable vehicle, designed to be just good enough to get us into court, where they can drag things on for another month before sending it to the Governor to set an election date even later in the year. And, because we will have to address it no matter how weak it is, it's also designed to bleed us further financially and sow doubt in the minds of our allies.

It's ironic that a man who has shown so little consideration for the Constitutional rights of Coloradans is suddenly so fixated on Constitutional verbiage but this is what they do. They play games and piss away other people's lives and money to drive their agenda a little further down the road. They don't give a shit about Constitutional rights but they'll gladly play the "letter of the law" game when it suits them, making a complete mockery of the beliefs we cherish, knowing that we're honor-bound to obey the rules we've set while they slink around them. "Everyone has a seat at the table" until you disagree and then they desperately scramble for fifteen different ways to pretend they don't hear you.

They held hearings to "let the public be heard" on the matter of gun laws - and then ignored the overwhelming chorus of "NO!" They couldn't get people to stop signing the recall petition so now they're trying to throw the whole thing out, again silencing the voices of over ten thousand citizens. If these laws were truly what Coloradans wanted, why not put them on the public ballot instead of ramming them down our throats despite our protests? If you truly believe that you did the right thing, why not face your constituency in a recall? Much like the argument for the bullshit background checks you forced on us, if you have nothing to hide, you have nothing to fear - right?

I'm trying to be rational and clear in my writing but I have to tell you I am so blindingly pissed right now, it's not even funny. Who are they to ignore the very people they are supposed to represent?!? We need to stop them right here, right now. I don't care if it's one man, we need to show that it can be done, that citizens hold the power to push back. We are a test case in almost every aspect of this recall process and are shaping legal precedent for taking power back from legislators who choose hubris over honor.

The help and support we’ve gotten from this community has been instrumental so far and the last thing I want to do is come across like a mooch but I’m swallowing my pride and doing my beggar routine again (Striker-approved). We don’t know how much we’re going to need this time but we are going to need funds to survive the stall tactics and attrition in the courts. Several of you IMed me over the past week to see if we still needed donations. At the time, I said we were waiting to see if we were still in the fight before accepting any more generosity but now I know – we are, we do and we’ll be reaching out to see if you’re still willing and able to contribute. For everyone else, whether you’ve donated before or are just hearing about this, we can use the help. If you can, please donate here. If you can’t, please spread the word about what’s happening – send people to this thread, to our website or to our Facebook page. 

https://www.basicfreedomdefensefund.org/

https://www.facebook.com/ColoradoAccountability
